# research-corpus-audit-parallel-agent-pattern — History

## v1.1.0 (2026-04-13)

**Changed by:** TurboQuant (Idea 5.1) per-idea Myrmidon swarm review session
**Verification:** verified-local

### What changed
- Extended "When to Use" to include per-idea KV cache quantization review
- Added 2 new Failed Attempts: "Trust 32K ctx label" and "Trust FlashInfer 4× for total TPOT"
- Added "KV Cache Quantization Numerical Checklist" to Results & Parameters
- Added "Realistic TPOT Improvement Table" with pre-computed values for A1/A2/B
- Added second "Verified On" row for TurboQuant review session
- Updated description to mention KV cache / quantization numerical correctness
- Added history frontmatter field
- Bumped version 1.0.0 → 1.1.0

### Why
Corpus-level audit (v1.0.0) catches structural compliance but misses per-idea numerical
errors. The TurboQuant review found two critical inherited errors that pass corpus audit
but are wrong: (1) context length mislabeling (68.7 GB labeled "32K ctx" but computed
with 262K tokens), (2) TPOT overstatement (claiming "2×-3×" when correct accounting of
weight bandwidth gives ~1.6×). These error patterns will recur across all KV-related ideas
(5.1, 5.2, 5.5, 5.6, etc.). The checklist prevents re-discovering them in future reviews.

